{"sequence":19,"timestamp":"2026-04-17T07:53:26.341416842Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-81165722","body":"finding_summary: The new prompt tells the model to \"assign priority using P1 ... P2 ... P3\" at `src/contexts/workspace_governance/template_catalog.rs:341`, but the MilestoneBundle contract expects `priority` to be a numeric field (`1=P1, 2=P2, ...`) at `src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs:1144-1146`. That is conflicting guidance for the same field and can drive schema-invalid milestone bundles on backends that do not hard-coerce structured output.\naffected_files: [\"src/contexts/workspace_governance/template_catalog.rs\", \"src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs\"]\nremediation_hint: Reword the prompt to request numeric priority values (`1`, `2`, `3`) while explaining their P1/P2/P3 meaning.","dedup_key":"1e37529890f07626714e24494e2b7aacc671fc21307089b1f35ebe4291313349","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260417072108","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":20,"timestamp":"2026-04-17T07:53:26.349971548Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-fbafd881","body":"finding_summary: The new `validate_dependency_graph()` helper is not actually safe on malformed bundles. It calls `dependency_graph_analysis()` (`src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs:838-949`), which canonicalizes IDs without running full validation (`src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs:1022-1046`), and `dependency_graph_analysis_from_canonical()` then inserts bead IDs into a `BTreeMap` with silent overwrite semantics (`src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs:714-717`). If two beads normalize to the same ID, the later one wins and the helper can return `Ok(())` or compute the graph against the wrong node instead of reporting the malformed input.\naffected_files: [\"src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs\"]\nremediation_hint: Base `validate_dependency_graph()` on `validated_canonical_bundle()` or explicitly reject duplicate normalized bead IDs before building `bead_index`.","dedup_key":"ccc55999d0f306e05fee3eba0df7358b9da0b93c60fe0224907d134dc0fe0138","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260417072108","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
